18/05/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Acting President Nicolae Vacaroiu signed the law on establishing the National Integrity Agency on Thursday (May 17th). 
The agency will oversee the activities of the all civil servants -- including members of Parliament -- monitor their asset declarations, and look for conflicts of interest. 
It can impose sanctions, including confiscation of illegal assets, and can bar violators from holding public office. 
Establishing the agency is in line with government efforts to eliminate corruption. 
(Nine O'clock - 18/05/07; Mediafax, Rompres - 17/05/07)
